            .col-sm-4
              .service-box
                .service-icon
                  span
                    img(src="icons/ico-cernvm.png")
                .service-desc
                  h5 You install CernVM WebAPI
                  p
                    | The first time you join the challenge, you will be prompted to install an application called “CernVM WebAPI”. This takes care of delivering the required software for the challenge to your machine.
                  p
                    em What is this, really?
                    br
                    small
                      | This is a tiny system service (about 1MB) which provides the interface between the web browser and a Virtual Machine in your computer.
            .col-sm-4
              .service-box
                .service-icon
                  span
                    img(src="icons/ico-virtualbox.png")
                .service-desc
                  h5 CernVM WebAPI installs VirtualBox
                  p
                    | We have packed all the scientific software required to run the challenge into a compact, virtual computer. Virtualbox is a free, open-source software that runs this virtual computer.
                  p
                    em Why is this necessary?
                    br
                    small
                      | The scientific software that we use runs only on Linux. That’s why we packed our Linux distribution in a virtual machine so it can run on almost any operating system.
            .col-sm-4
              .service-box
                .service-icon
                  span
                    img(src="icons/icon-antimatter-01.png")
                .service-desc
                  h5 You are now in control
                  p
                    | After all this software is installed on your computer, just click “Start” on the interface and join the challenge! Please be patient, it might take a few minutes to see something happening...
                  p
                    em What can I control?
                    br
                    small
                      | You can define how much CPU and RAM you allocate to the project, by clicking on the gear icon next to the start button. Don’t forget to click Apply!

      p &nbsp;
      p &nbsp;
