            .text-left
              #accordion.panel-group
                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordionOne")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> To take part in the challenge do I need to have my computer switched on all the time?
                  #accordionOne.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                            | <strong>A:</strong> No! In fact, to avoid wasting energy, you should only participate while you are doing other stuff on your computer. For example trying out some of the other #[a.btn-scroll(href="#more") CERN-related public participation projects]. 
                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion2")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> How much effort is involved for me to be part of the challenge? 
                  #accordion2.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                            | <strong>A:</strong> None! The virtual machine in your computer takes care of everything and sends us results periodically. It restarts automatically every time you restart your computer. 

                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion3")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> Why is this just a fifteen-day challenge? What happens afterwards?
                  #accordion3.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                      | <strong>A:</strong> We're building up a database of results that will help people play a game about particle physics, to be launched next year. Fifteen days will produce enough data. If you want to be the first to know once the game is launched, #[a.btn-scroll(href="#contact") drop us a line].

                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion4")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> Are there any prizes involved in this challenge? 
                  #accordion4.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                      | <strong>A:</strong> As computers around the world return results, the Timeline on this page will gradually fill out. If a result from your computer comes at just the right time to unlock a historical fact, you'll get a special mention on the timeline. 

                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion5")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> Will I get any feedback about how much I have contributed personally to the project?  
                  #accordion5.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                      | <strong>A:</strong> Once you've got the project running, you'll be able to see your progress on a web page that comes up every time you click Start Computing on this challenge page. 

                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion6")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> Does the software I install respect my privacy? And how do I get rid of it, if I want to? 
                  #accordion6.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                      | <strong>A:</strong> The only data about you that we keep on our server is a unique identifier for your computer, which we use to attribute your contributions, and your login username, but not the password. To uninstall at any time, see #[a(href="http://google.com") these instructions].

                .panel.panel-default
                  .panel-heading
                    h4.panel-title
                            a(data-toggle="collapse", data-parent="#accordion", href="#accordion7")
                              | <strong>Q:</strong> Can I install this challenge on several computers, and see their total performance? 
                  #accordion7.panel-collapse.collapse
                    .panel-body
                      | <strong>A:</strong> Yes, just make sure you login with the same account everywhere, so you can aggregate your results. 



